OL,7,FJeremy Hunt outlined a series of
OL,8,Freforms to disability benefits in
OL,9,FWednesday's budget, describing them as
OL,10,Fthe "biggest change to our welfare
OL,11,Fsystem in a decade".
OL,13,FThe Chancellor announced the scrapping
OL,14,Fof the work capability assessment (WCA)
OL,15,Fto determine eligibility for sickness
OL,16,Fbenefits, along with a new employment
OL,17,Fscheme for disabled people called
OL,18,FUniversal Support.
OL,3,CDisability benefit changes in Budget:
OL,4,CWork capability assessment, sanctions,
OL,5,CUniversal Support
